MAD DOG N JOE took the field inside to the first turn, had a slight advantage setting the pace down the backside, was headed outside midway on the far turn and retreated on the fence in mid-stretch.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: ENJOYTHESILENT switched outside foes up the backstretch, advanced rapidly four then five wide on the turn, took charge outside the three-sixteenths, quickly spurted clear under urging, was eased up in the final stages. CHASING TROUBLE settled off the pace, raced outside foes four then five wide on the the turn swinging seven deep into upper stretch, secured the place while no threat to the winner. SO CALLED VACATION moved forward to engage the leader, dueled inside that one but off the fence, came out a bit in upper stretch after being overtaken, kept on to hold show honors. JIM'S HOPE got away a step slowly, angled in and steadily advanced inside rivals up the backstretch, was within range on the turn, came out a bit in upper stretch, faced traffic in behind runners briefly nearing the sixteenth pole and ran on willingly. GRAND AMBITION stalked from outside with good forward position early, went four wide on the turn urged and moving quickly to bid at the quarter pole, could not sustain the effort in the stretch. ROCK BULLET settled off the pace racing just off the rail, moved out four wide past the quarter pole, came out further in upper stretch and ran on. HEMLO GOLD broke in the air and quite slowly, moved up to regain contact with the field inside, saved ground on the turn, came out a bit for the drive, needed more. STREET SERENADE shifted in racing near the inside toward the rear just off the rail, ran on. QUIET VISTA failed to threaten racing off the inside part of the track. FOREST STAR was outside foes toward the back three to four wide on the turn, swung eight deep, failed to rally. BROTHER BELEN got away well, set the early tempo, was soon engaged by an inside foe, dueled with that one to the three-eighths then steadily retreated and was not persevered with in the stretch.
